name: Carbohydrate
description: Carbohydrates (or saccharides) are organic compounds with the empirical formula Cm(H2O)n. The carbohydrates  are divided into four chemical groupings: monosaccharides, disaccharides, oligosaccharides, and polysaccharides. The monosaccharides and disaccharides are commonly referred to as sugars. [Wikipedia]
